I have made this several times, and always use whole slices of tuna, then cut after searing. Once, I made this for wine-food pairing party, where we were passing appetizers. So, it all needed to be made ahead of time. I seared the tuna (rare) in the morning then wrapped tightly in plastic wrap. An hour or so ahead, I cut it into small squares, threaded with the ginger, then used baggie with a little corner cut off to put a little sqiggle of wasabi may on each peice. Then refridgerated again. It was very pretty and our guests loved it...even many who were convinced they would never like sushi! (Also, after making this several times, I think it is far far better as an appetizer chilled...but as an entree I would still serve it warm.)

