Rating: 3
This was very tasty, and was devoured by boring relatives whose usual response to seafood is "eew, fish." Indeed, in anticipation of such a response, I made only half a batch, which turned out to be instructive: beware, the full recipe requires some really quick work to sear and turn 28 cubes six times each in less than two minutes. I found I could barely cook and turn half the recipe without overcooking the tuna; the whole thing would have been a disaster. Finally, not wanting to spend $18 per pound for fresh tuna that most of my relatives wouldn't know from pollock, I bought a small individually frozen tuna steak at a fraction of the price. It worked out fine.

